article.headline: Belmont 88, Navy 71
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Steve Drabyn and Adam Mark each scored 22 points Monday night to lead Belmont to an 88-71 win over Navy. Drabyn, who led the nation with a 95.1 free throw percentage last season, made 11 of 11 free throws to extend his streak to 52 in a row. He scored 18 points in the first half when Belmont grabbed a 48-40 lead. Mark, who led the nation in field goal shooting last season, was just 8-for-18 against Navy but had 13 second-half points. Freshman Josh Goodwin added 16 points and Jese Snyder scored 11 for the Bruins (1-1). The Bruins were 12 for 23 from three-point range, with Goodwin hitting four and Drabyn and Snyder making three each. Kwame Ofori and David Hooper each scored 14 points to lead Navy (0-2). Matt Fannin added 13 points. Navy scored the first basket of the game, but Belmont scored the next 20 points -- Drabyn getting 14 in the stretch -- to build a 20-2 lead five minutes into the game. Navy battled back with a 14-0 run to close to 20-16, then tied the game at 27 and 29, with six minutes left in the half, before Belmont pulled back in front to stay. The Mids made 25 turnovers and Belmont shot 50 percent from the floor for the game and was 20 for 26 in free throws.
